    // CustomPresetActivity requires com.samsung.android.app.reminder.permission.action.ReminderPresetSettings
    component = ComponentName(
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder",
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.preset.CustomPresetActivity"
    )
    action = "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.action.ReminderPresetSettings"
    // again â€” no setPackage
}
// ...wrap with popover_intent as above
```

**3) adb one-liner sanity:**
```
adb shell am start -a android.intent.action.VIEW \
  -d "reminder://viewdetail/?fromBrief=true" \
  -n com.samsung.android.app.reminder/com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.view.DetailActivity \
  --es popover_intent "intent:#Intent;action=com.samsung.android.app.reminder.action.ReminderAddView;component=com.samsung.android.app.reminder/com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.add.AddActivity;S.uuid=deadbeef;end"
```

### Root-cause fixes
1. In `M.c`, reject the parsed Intent unless **both** `uri.getPackage()` equals `"com.samsung.android.app.reminder"` **and** `uri.getComponent() != null && uri.getComponent().getPackageName().equals("com.samsung.android.app.reminder")`. Additionally strip `uri.getSelector()` before returning to eliminate `SEL`-based redirection.
2. Replace the string-based "popover_intent" carrier with a Parcelable Intent extra validated against a hard allow-list of `(action, component)` tuples.
3. In the long term, do not use `Intent.parseUri` / `Intent.toUri` to cross trust boundaries â€” they are explicitly documented as unsafe for that.

