The `utils.d#invoke(Intent) â†’ String` extractor reads the `pending_data` extra (which, per the round-trip logic in `D.h(int,int,Intent)` at line 256, is set by real code as `intent.toUri(1)`). Three things combine to make this a fresh sink:

1. `pending_data` is a plain, **attacker-settable** String extra on the original intent delivered to `AddActivity` â€” there is no source check.
2. `Intent.parseUri(str3, 1)` uses `URI_INTENT_SCHEME`, so the rebuilt Intent carries attacker-chosen `component=`, `package=`, `action=`, `flags=`, `category=`, `extras=` â€” plus `SEL` (selector intent) if the attacker encodes one.
3. There is **no** `getPackage()` equality check and **no** `getComponent()` check (compare to V-008 in `M.c`, which at least checks `getPackage()`).

The reconstructed Intent is then handed to `this.h(requestCode, resultCode, uri)`:

```java
