## [V-010] AddDelegate `D.l` â€” Unchecked `getSerializableExtra("checkPresetIds")` Deserialisation

**File:** `sources/com/samsung/android/app/reminder/ui/detail/add/D.java` (line 367)
**Severity:** Mediumâ€“High (classic Java deserialisation reachable pre-Android-13 with attacker bytes; less severe on A13+ but still parses attacker Serializable).
**Class of flaw:** CWE-502 â€” Deserialisation of untrusted data.

### Summary
Early in `D.l(Intent)`, before any allow-list or caller check:
```java
bundle.putSerializable("checkPresetIds", this.f29992d.getSerializableExtra("checkPresetIds"));
```
`getSerializableExtra(String)` (no `Class<T>` argument) invokes `ObjectInputStream.readObject()` on attacker-supplied bytes on any Android version; on pre-13 it resolves arbitrary classes, and even on A13+ it still constructs attacker-chosen Serializable graphs reachable through the reminder app's classpath (which includes Gson, Firebase, Graph SDK, MSAL, CameraX â€” a large attack surface for readResolve / readExternal gadget chains).

### Attacker angle
Combined with V-001 (reaching AddActivity via DetailActivity), the attacker controls `checkPresetIds` on the incoming Intent. At minimum this grants:

* **Class-loading side-channel:** the attacker pins a named class on the reminder app's classpath via their serialised payload (resolvers called during readObject).
* **Gadget chain:** classic `readObject â†’ readResolve â†’ ...` chain â€” if any library on the classpath defines one, the attacker can trigger it. Samsung apps historically ship enough libraries (Firebase, Graph, MSAL, Gson TypeAdapters) for reachability.
* **DoS via nested Serializable** (exhaust heap by deeply-nested arrays).

### PoC (reachability)
```kotlin
val malicious: Serializable = buildMaliciousGadgetChain()    // e.g., Firebase ReplacingInputStream
val reach = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW).apply {
    setClassName(
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder",
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.view.DetailActivity"
    )
    data = Uri.parse("uuid://reminder.uuid/x")
    putExtra("checkPresetIds", malicious)
    addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK)
}
startActivity(reach)
```
Ensuring the redirect fires (V-001) then causes `D.l` to call `getSerializableExtra("checkPresetIds")` â†’ `readObject()` â†’ gadget.

### Root-cause fix
Replace with `getSerializableExtra("checkPresetIds", <ExactExpectedClass>.class)` (A13+ typed API) AND validate the resulting graph strictly (e.g., only `ArrayList<String>`). Better: use `getStringArrayListExtra("checkPresetIds")` â€” strings are not Serializable-deserialised.

