## [V-013] MainListActivity `k1(Intent)` â€” Debug-Build `sync_reminder_data` JSON â†’ DB Reminder Injection

**File:** `sources/com/samsung/android/app/reminder/ui/list/main/MainListActivity.java` (lines 1092â€“1182)
**Severity:** Medium (gated by `ro.build.type != "user"`) â€” but **critical on userdebug / engineer / internal-build devices** and leaves a trivial JSON-to-SQLite injection pipeline alive.
**Class of flaw:** CWE-489 (active debug code) + CWE-20 (unchecked JSON input â†’ DB writes) + CWE-502 flavour (structured data deserialised from untrusted source).

### Sink code
```java
public final void k1(final Intent intent) {
    if ("user".equals(SemSystemProperties.get("ro.build.type", "user"))
        || TextUtils.isEmpty(intent.getStringExtra("sync_reminder_data"))) {
        return;
    }
    ...
    JSONArray jSONArray = new JSONObject(intent.getStringExtra("sync_reminder_data")).getJSONArray("data");
    for (int i11 = 0; i11 < jSONArray.length(); i11++) {
        JSONObject jo = (JSONObject) jSONArray.get(i11);
        final String id   = jo.optString("id");
        final String desc = jo.getString("description");
        // parses date&time as "YYYY/MM/DD" or "YYYY/MM/DD/hhmm" into epoch ms
